analysis: The documents all relate to the withdrawal or revocation of withdrawal of public lands for resurvey, primarily in Wyoming, Colorado, and New Mexico. They all cite the act of June 25, 1910, as amended by the act of August 24, 1912, and reference the act of March 3, 1909. Some orders establish withdrawals pending resurveys, while others revoke previous withdrawal orders after resurveys have been completed. The documents span the presidencies of Herbert Hoover and Franklin D. Roosevelt.
title: Land Withdrawal and Resurvey Orders
